  "text": "Total RNAs from brain tissue samples and BV2 cells were isolated using RNeasy kits (QIAGEN, Hilden, Germany); all samples were reverse transcribed using RT premix (Intron, Sungnam, Korea). Real-time PCR was performed using the iQ5 real-time PCR detection system (Bio-Rad, Hercules, CA) and SYBR green was used to detect amplification products, as described previously [CITATION_1] . The reaction conditions used were; initial denaturation at 95uC for 10 min, 40 amplification cycles [denaturation at 95uC for 10 s, annealing at 56uC for 30 s, and elongation at 72uC for 30 s], followed by one cycle at 72uC for 5 min. Data analysis was performed using iQ TM 5 optical system software (Bio-Rad). Primer sequences used for GAPDH, IFN-c, TGF-b, and IL-10 are shown in Table S1 .",
